  "response": "As of 2023, living in Libya remains challenging due to ongoing political instability and conflicts. Key points include:\n\n1. Political Situation\n- Divided government between east and west\n- Ongoing tensions between rival factions\n- Lack of unified central authority\n\n2. Economic Conditions\n- High unemployment\n- Economic instability\n- Inflation and currency devaluation\n- Limited public services\n\n3. Security\n- Periodic armed conflicts\n- Presence of militia groups\n- Potential for sudden violence\n- Weak law enforcement\n\n4. Basic Infrastructure\n- Inconsistent electricity supply\n- Limited healthcare services\n- Disrupted educational systems\n- Challenges with water and sanitation\n\n5. Social Life\n- Cultural restrictions\n- Limited freedom of expression\n- Conservative social norms\n- Impact of years of conflict on social structures\n\n6. International Relations\n- Ongoing diplomatic efforts to stabilize the country\n- Limited international investment\n- Humanitarian challenges\n\nThe situation remains fluid, with potential for both improvement and further instability. Conditions can vary significantly between different regions of the country.\n\nFor the most current and detailed information, consulting recent diplomatic reports or humanitarian organization updates is recommended.",
